RoS director of commercial services Kenny Crawford said picture over the last 10 years was one of "highs and lows".
He added: "Activity in the property market gives us an insight into what's going on in the Scottish economy, which is possible thanks to Registers of Scotland's digital land register."
Last month, Office for National Statistics figures found house prices in Scotland had experienced their highest annual increase since 2007.
